<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="199" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.543 C 42/6.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Reinsch</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 351.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Department has received your No. 770 of September 30, 1915, and
                            approves your course in pointing out to the Chinese Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs that the case was one between Americans and Chinese in which no
                            other nationality was involved, and requesting for the Legation’s files
                            another statement of the settlement, which should not confuse the
                            question at issue by irrelevant references to third parties.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>